# Interview Questions for Panel – Data Analyst

**Note:** The uploaded materials provided only the recruitment brief. No candidate screening summary was included, so candidate-specific clarification questions linked to identified gaps could not be tailored. The questions below are based only on the role criteria and responsibilities in the recruitment brief.

| Question | Purpose | Linked criterion or gap |
|---|---|---|
| Can you walk us through your background and explain how your experience aligns with this Data Analyst role? | Assess overall role fit and relevance of prior experience. | 1–3 years of experience in a Data Analyst or similar role |
| Tell us about a recent analysis project where your work supported business decision-making. What was your approach and impact? | Test ability to analyse data and produce useful business insights. | Support business decision-making; analyse and interpret data |
| Describe your process for collecting, cleaning, and validating data from multiple sources. | Assess technical discipline and data quality practices. | Collect, clean, and validate data from different sources |
| How do you make sure the data you are reporting on is accurate and reliable? | Evaluate attention to detail and validation methods. | Detail orientation; data validation |
| Can you give an example of how you identified a trend, issue, or business opportunity from data? | Test analytical thinking and insight generation. | Analyse data to identify trends, issues, and opportunities |
| What experience do you have preparing regular reports or dashboards for management or business teams? | Assess reporting and dashboard capability. | Prepare regular reports and dashboards |
| Which dashboard tools have you used, such as Power BI or Tableau, and how have you used them in practice? | Confirm hands-on dashboard tool experience. | Experience with Power BI, Tableau, or similar tools |
| What types of KPIs have you reported on, and how did you decide which metrics mattered most? | Assess KPI understanding and business judgement. | Understanding of KPI reporting and dashboard development |
| How would you explain a complex data finding to a non-technical stakeholder? | Test communication and ability to translate technical findings clearly. | Ability to present findings clearly to non-technical stakeholders |
| Tell us about a time you had to turn analysis into a practical recommendation. What was your recommendation and what happened next? | Assess ability to move from insight to action. | Translate data findings into clear recommendations |
| What is your level of confidence with Excel, and which functions or techniques do you use most often? | Check core technical capability. | Strong skills in Excel |
| What kinds of SQL queries have you written in your previous roles? | Check core technical capability and depth of SQL experience. | Strong skills in SQL |
| Tell us about a time you supported an ad-hoc request from a team such as Sales, Marketing, Finance, or Operations. How did you manage it? | Assess responsiveness, stakeholder support, and prioritisation. | Support ad-hoc analysis requests across departments |
| How do you clarify a vague request from a stakeholder before starting your analysis? | Test communication, problem framing, and stakeholder management. | Support ad-hoc requests; communicate clearly |
| Describe a situation where you found an error or inconsistency in data. What did you do? | Assess attention to detail and problem-solving. | Analytical and detail-oriented |
| Have you used Python or R in your work? If so, what did you use it for? | Explore preferred but non-essential technical capability. | Preferred: experience with Python or R |
| What experience have you had working with business or operational data? | Assess preferred domain relevance. | Preferred: experience with business or operational data |
| Tell us about a time when your findings were challenged by a stakeholder. How did you respond? | Assess communication, resilience, and credibility. | Present findings clearly; stakeholder engagement |
| How do you manage competing deadlines when multiple teams request analysis at the same time? | Test organisation and work prioritisation. | Support multiple business teams; role suitability |
| What interests you about this role, and why do you believe you would be effective in it? | Assess motivation and final role fit. | Overall suitability |

## Candidate-specific clarification questions
Because no candidate screening summary was provided, the panel may wish to add targeted clarification questions once the candidate's gaps or unclear areas are known. Typical examples include:

| Question | Purpose | Linked criterion or gap |
|---|---|---|
| Can you expand on your level of hands-on experience with SQL in your most recent role? | Clarify depth of skill if SQL experience appears limited or unclear in the screening summary. | Candidate gap to confirm: SQL capability |
| Can you talk us through a dashboard you built yourself and the tools you used? | Clarify ownership and practical dashboard experience if this is not clear from the screening summary. | Candidate gap to confirm: Power BI/Tableau/dashboard development |
| Your application mentions analysis experience. Can you explain how often you presented findings to non-technical stakeholders? | Clarify communication exposure if stakeholder presentation experience is unclear. | Candidate gap to confirm: communication with non-technical stakeholders |
| Can you describe the types of business data you worked with and the decisions that data informed? | Clarify relevance of prior data experience if industry or data context is unclear. | Candidate gap to confirm: business or operational data experience |
